1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:10,000
[English subtitles are available]

2
00:01:00,990 --> 00:01:04,680
[We Are Young]

3
00:01:04,819 --> 00:01:07,530
[Episode 43]

4
00:01:08,620 --> 00:01:12,580
You felt guilty and wanted to make amends.

5
00:01:14,220 --> 00:01:16,450
So you chose to care for me,

6
00:01:16,750 --> 00:01:18,180
to bring me up.

7
00:01:19,030 --> 00:01:21,900
You thought I wouldn't forgive you,

8
00:01:22,789 --> 00:01:24,810
so you hide it from me.

9
00:01:25,390 --> 00:01:26,900
And now, because of you,

10
00:01:27,030 --> 00:01:28,900
because you can't face me,

11
00:01:29,150 --> 00:01:30,500
you won't let me see Duan Ran.

12
00:01:30,500 --> 00:01:32,150
Everything is about your needs

13
00:01:32,150 --> 00:01:33,370
and your wants.

14
00:01:33,940 --> 00:01:36,220
Did you ever consider how I'd feel?

15
00:02:14,310 --> 00:02:15,490
Xi Xi.

16
00:02:19,870 --> 00:02:21,460
I beg you.

17
00:02:21,900 --> 00:02:24,180
Stop tormenting me.

18
00:04:09,180 --> 00:04:10,650
Good evening, Mr Duan Jr.

19
00:04:12,260 --> 00:04:13,250
Madam Li.

20
00:04:13,620 --> 00:04:14,770
Have you seen Xi Xi?

21
00:04:14,950 --> 00:04:16,649
No. I was busy the whole day.

22
00:04:17,060 --> 00:04:18,390
Carry on with your work.

23
00:05:06,030 --> 00:05:07,370
This is the one.

24
00:05:19,060 --> 00:05:20,050
Mr Yu.

25
00:05:21,710 --> 00:05:22,820
Mr Duan Jr.

26
00:05:23,630 --> 00:05:25,210
Have you seen Xi Xi?

27
00:05:29,430 --> 00:05:31,450
You're looking for Xi Xi?

28
00:05:32,220 --> 00:05:33,850
Aunt Zhou was here today.

29
00:05:33,940 --> 00:05:35,370
She took Xi Xi out.

30
00:05:38,340 --> 00:05:39,490
I see.

31
00:05:39,590 --> 00:05:40,920
Carry on with your work.

32
00:05:42,810 --> 00:05:43,800
Mr Duan Jr.

33
00:05:47,980 --> 00:05:49,930
Mr Duan, Mr Duan.

34
00:05:53,310 --> 00:05:56,100
Mr Duan, I want to talk to you.

35
00:05:58,260 --> 00:05:59,500
Just call me Duan Ran.

36
00:05:59,590 --> 00:06:02,930
I should call you Mr Yu from now on.

37
00:06:06,100 --> 00:06:09,860
Mr Duan, I know you hate me.

38
00:06:10,780 --> 00:06:12,650
I also hate myself.

39
00:06:13,380 --> 00:06:14,590
I don't deserve the title.

40
00:06:14,590 --> 00:06:16,250
Please don't mock me.

41
00:06:16,780 --> 00:06:18,330
I really had no choice.

42
00:06:20,660 --> 00:06:21,980
Voting

43
00:06:23,100 --> 00:06:25,020
is all about making a choice.

44
00:06:25,260 --> 00:06:27,120
What do you mean you had no choice?

45
00:06:27,470 --> 00:06:29,330
I'm not trying to explain myself.

46
00:06:30,220 --> 00:06:31,370
I'll repay your debt

47
00:06:33,030 --> 00:06:34,930
with my life.

48
00:06:35,260 --> 00:06:36,890
What is there to repay?

49
00:06:37,490 --> 00:06:38,890
I must repay.

50
00:06:39,909 --> 00:06:40,900
Mr Duan.

51
00:06:41,470 --> 00:06:43,580
I may be a cowardly piece of trash,

52
00:06:43,710 --> 00:06:45,409
but I can be recycled.

53
00:06:46,310 --> 00:06:47,300
You know what?

54
00:06:47,500 --> 00:06:49,610
After I voted for Shen Ding Ding,

55
00:06:49,700 --> 00:06:52,210
I told myself enough is enough.

56
00:06:52,470 --> 00:06:55,260
I no longer owe the Shen family anything.

57
00:06:55,860 --> 00:06:57,150
The reason that I became

58
00:06:57,150 --> 00:06:58,860
a puppet CEO

59
00:07:00,990 --> 00:07:03,150
is to protect the others
who are still here.

60
00:07:03,150 --> 00:07:04,540
I want to protect Xi Xi.

61
00:07:04,660 --> 00:07:07,590
I want to protect Mr Five and
those who are still here.

62
00:07:08,260 --> 00:07:10,020
I can protect Rui for you.

63
00:07:11,500 --> 00:07:13,250
Now that you mention it,

64
00:07:13,990 --> 00:07:19,370
our friends and colleagues

65
00:07:19,740 --> 00:07:22,050
do need you here to protect them.

66
00:07:22,540 --> 00:07:23,860
Don't worry.

67
00:07:25,500 --> 00:07:26,890
That's good to know.

68
00:07:34,470 --> 00:07:36,420
At this point,

69
00:07:38,710 --> 00:07:40,200
what are your plans?

70
00:07:41,100 --> 00:07:42,650
I don't have any plans.

71
00:07:43,909 --> 00:07:46,420
I don't know what plans I should have.

72
00:07:50,500 --> 00:07:52,370
I've been thinking.

73
00:07:55,190 --> 00:07:57,250
Why did I become an entrepreneur?

74
00:07:59,060 --> 00:08:00,740
Why?

75
00:08:02,530 --> 00:08:04,050
To prove myself to others?

76
00:08:05,590 --> 00:08:06,740
Who knows.

77
00:08:07,660 --> 00:08:09,060
You have no obligation

78
00:08:09,140 --> 00:08:11,890
to prove anything to anyone.

79
00:08:11,990 --> 00:08:13,610
You are who you are.

80
00:08:14,470 --> 00:08:17,070
You've always been
our most important friend.

81
00:08:17,150 --> 00:08:18,650
You're our pillar

82
00:08:18,820 --> 00:08:20,300
and our compass.

83
00:08:20,580 --> 00:08:22,650
We need you to lead us, Mr Duan.

84
00:08:26,630 --> 00:08:28,050
Lead?

85
00:08:28,940 --> 00:08:31,500
I don't even know what my goals
are anymore.

86
00:08:31,580 --> 00:08:33,210
How can I lead?

87
00:08:35,140 --> 00:08:37,299
I have to find my direction first.

88
00:08:38,510 --> 00:08:40,650
Once you've found your direction,

89
00:08:41,260 --> 00:08:42,450
let me know.

90
00:08:42,870 --> 00:08:44,600
I will give you my full support.

91
00:08:45,630 --> 00:08:48,010
Take care of that leg first.

92
00:08:49,340 --> 00:08:51,930
If it doesn't recover,

93
00:08:52,020 --> 00:08:53,890
how will you support me?

94
00:08:56,660 --> 00:08:57,760
Enough talking.

95
00:08:59,070 --> 00:09:01,380
Standing too long is bad for your leg.

96
00:09:02,580 --> 00:09:04,130
Take care of that leg.

97
00:09:48,830 --> 00:09:52,500
Mum, where did you and Xi Xi go yesterday?

98
00:09:54,020 --> 00:09:55,620
We hadn't met in a while.

99
00:09:55,750 --> 00:09:57,420
So I took her for a massage.

100
00:09:59,070 --> 00:10:00,870
That's pretty late for a massage.

101
00:10:00,870 --> 00:10:04,380
Xi Xi didn't answer my call this morning.

102
00:10:04,990 --> 00:10:06,690
Isn't she up yet?

103
00:10:08,510 --> 00:10:10,330
We'll be more mindful next time.

104
00:10:11,700 --> 00:10:13,700
Duan, what's your plan today?

105
00:10:13,780 --> 00:10:14,770
Me?

106
00:10:17,310 --> 00:10:18,500
I'm going fishing.

107
00:10:19,870 --> 00:10:21,050
I have to go.

108
00:10:23,190 --> 00:10:24,180
Ran Ran.

109
00:10:25,990 --> 00:10:27,450
Let's go fishing.

110
00:10:27,580 --> 00:10:29,770
No thanks.
The weather is too hot.

111
00:10:31,700 --> 00:10:33,700
You want to stay here and
let her nag at you

112
00:10:33,700 --> 00:10:34,870
or you want to fish with me?

113
00:10:34,870 --> 00:10:36,500
Think about it.

114
00:10:38,540 --> 00:10:40,070
Is that how you advise your son?

115
00:10:40,070 --> 00:10:41,420
I'll go fishing then.

116
00:10:42,750 --> 00:10:45,010
Is that how you advise our son?

117
00:10:51,710 --> 00:10:53,380
[Resignation Letter]

118
00:11:02,390 --> 00:11:04,540
-Mr Ding.
-Ms Ouyang.

119
00:11:04,990 --> 00:11:06,380
How's your weekend?

120
00:11:06,950 --> 00:11:08,010
It was good.

121
00:11:08,270 --> 00:11:10,330
I'm meeting some investors tonight.

122
00:11:10,450 --> 00:11:11,370
Big shots.

123
00:11:11,460 --> 00:11:12,780
Are you interested to join?

124
00:11:12,780 --> 00:11:14,050
I'm a small fry.

125
00:11:14,140 --> 00:11:16,450
I'd better not join you big shots.

126
00:11:16,580 --> 00:11:17,490
What's wrong?

127
00:11:17,580 --> 00:11:19,020
You're always shunning me.

128
00:11:19,020 --> 00:11:20,450
It's only dinner.

129
00:11:21,630 --> 00:11:22,740
Mr Ding.

130
00:11:23,270 --> 00:11:24,860
I thank you for your offer.

131
00:11:24,950 --> 00:11:26,180
But today

132
00:11:26,340 --> 00:11:27,980
I have something important.

133
00:11:28,100 --> 00:11:30,770
I'm resigning.

134
00:11:33,390 --> 00:11:34,810
Why?

135
00:11:36,430 --> 00:11:37,980
For personal reasons.

136
00:11:38,310 --> 00:11:40,370
I'll proceed with the handover

137
00:11:40,460 --> 00:11:42,810
with Mr Yu.

138
00:11:43,270 --> 00:11:45,800
I plan to let Xi Xi take over
the private label.

139
00:11:45,830 --> 00:11:47,900
I have full authority
on the private label.

140
00:11:47,900 --> 00:11:49,290
You know that.

141
00:11:49,540 --> 00:11:51,490
Do you hate me that much?

142
00:11:51,900 --> 00:11:53,860
We are colleagues.

143
00:11:53,950 --> 00:11:55,540
Hate is such a strong word.

144
00:11:55,630 --> 00:11:58,780
But I wouldn't say we're destined
for each other, either.

145
00:11:58,780 --> 00:12:00,450
Destiny

146
00:12:00,870 --> 00:12:02,690
isn't something you can force.

147
00:12:02,870 --> 00:12:04,070
Hope you understand.

148
00:12:05,700 --> 00:12:07,810
Alright. It's your loss.

149
00:12:07,950 --> 00:12:09,150
If it makes you happy.

150
00:12:27,460 --> 00:12:28,500
Xi Xi.

151
00:12:28,780 --> 00:12:30,320
Why are you late today?

152
00:12:31,860 --> 00:12:33,500
What happened?

153
00:12:33,660 --> 00:12:34,740
I'm fine.

154
00:12:35,140 --> 00:12:36,130
Did you hear?

155
00:12:37,390 --> 00:12:39,570
Ms Ouyang resigned.

156
00:12:57,630 --> 00:12:58,930
I heard the news.

157
00:12:59,630 --> 00:13:00,940
You resigned.

158
00:13:07,510 --> 00:13:08,650
It's about Duan Ran.

159
00:13:13,450 --> 00:13:15,130
I realised

160
00:13:15,390 --> 00:13:17,190
when it comes to relationships,

161
00:13:17,390 --> 00:13:18,930
clinging on

162
00:13:19,020 --> 00:13:20,380
only leads to misery.

163
00:13:20,820 --> 00:13:21,940
But if you're

164
00:13:22,020 --> 00:13:23,890
always miserable,

165
00:13:24,310 --> 00:13:25,810
you can't let go.

166
00:13:26,950 --> 00:13:28,180
I'm happy now.

167
00:13:30,750 --> 00:13:33,500
Spending the past six months with you

168
00:13:34,010 --> 00:13:36,120
wasn't easy for me.

169
00:13:36,750 --> 00:13:38,370
Since I knew Duan Ran,

170
00:13:38,460 --> 00:13:39,790
there's never been a day

171
00:13:39,950 --> 00:13:42,380
that was easy for me.

172
00:13:44,460 --> 00:13:47,060
Because you're always on his mind

173
00:13:47,270 --> 00:13:49,490
and you're very important to him.

174
00:13:49,580 --> 00:13:51,930
Moreover, with the passing of time,

175
00:13:52,020 --> 00:13:54,010
you two have become more important

176
00:13:54,100 --> 00:13:55,620
to each other.

177
00:13:56,340 --> 00:13:57,620
What can I do?

178
00:13:59,100 --> 00:14:00,900
Never mind, it's in the past now.

179
00:14:06,750 --> 00:14:09,650
By the way, I have two things to tell you.

180
00:14:10,140 --> 00:14:11,180
First,

181
00:14:11,270 --> 00:14:12,940
it's about Vine.

182
00:14:13,700 --> 00:14:15,780
I wanted to pass it to Duan Ran.

183
00:14:15,870 --> 00:14:18,980
But he wants me to pass it to you.

184
00:14:20,190 --> 00:14:21,380
Second,

185
00:14:22,100 --> 00:14:23,420
it's this.

186
00:14:28,310 --> 00:14:30,380
I thought I had lost it.

187
00:14:31,780 --> 00:14:35,420
Let me say two more things.

188
00:14:36,660 --> 00:14:38,010
I think in future,

189
00:14:38,100 --> 00:14:40,250
when you face setbacks at work,

190
00:14:40,340 --> 00:14:43,690
you should be more tactful

191
00:14:43,830 --> 00:14:45,130
and more flexible.

192
00:14:45,310 --> 00:14:47,210
Learn how to communicate better.

193
00:14:47,340 --> 00:14:49,340
Don't go head-to-head all the time.

194
00:14:50,460 --> 00:14:52,860
As for matters of the heart,

195
00:14:53,510 --> 00:14:57,010
just give yourself some time
if you can't find the answer yet.

196
00:15:03,950 --> 00:15:05,500
Thanks, Ms Ouyang.

197
00:15:08,860 --> 00:15:11,250
If we get the chance,

198
00:15:11,460 --> 00:15:13,520
I hope to collaborate with you again.

199
00:15:13,660 --> 00:15:16,690
If we hadn't gotten a new boss,

200
00:15:16,890 --> 00:15:18,500
I wouldn't have resigned.

201
00:15:53,700 --> 00:15:55,860
There you are. Have a seat.

202
00:16:01,070 --> 00:16:03,070
I'm impressed.
Everything feels brand new.

203
00:16:03,070 --> 00:16:04,900
Ever since that phone call we had,

204
00:16:04,900 --> 00:16:06,370
I've been thinking,

205
00:16:06,460 --> 00:16:08,120
"What is divine assistance?"

206
00:16:08,460 --> 00:16:09,780
With you coming here to help me,

207
00:16:09,780 --> 00:16:11,650
that is divine assistance.

208
00:16:13,100 --> 00:16:14,140
So for the past two days,

209
00:16:14,140 --> 00:16:15,100
I gave Cloud Live

210
00:16:15,190 --> 00:16:17,300
a complete makeover.

211
00:16:17,460 --> 00:16:18,660
I've figured it all out.

212
00:16:18,660 --> 00:16:22,250
This place will become Rui's asylum.

213
00:16:23,270 --> 00:16:26,010
Impressive. You're getting smarter.

214
00:16:26,780 --> 00:16:28,010
No. It's just that

215
00:16:28,340 --> 00:16:31,420
we both know each other well.

216
00:16:33,690 --> 00:16:34,700
Well?

217
00:16:34,780 --> 00:16:36,270
Cloud's account will be reactivated soon.

218
00:16:36,270 --> 00:16:37,980
Is everything back on track?

219
00:16:38,510 --> 00:16:39,540
Almost.

220
00:16:42,820 --> 00:16:43,950
I went around this place just now.

221
00:16:43,950 --> 00:16:46,280
But I didn't see Cola and Little Duckling.

222
00:16:47,510 --> 00:16:49,090
They've resigned.

223
00:16:51,670 --> 00:16:54,530
[Duan Ran's Office]

224
00:16:54,460 --> 00:16:56,860
I've taken care of the liquidated damages.

225
00:16:57,870 --> 00:17:00,770
We had been really worried

226
00:17:00,900 --> 00:17:03,160
since we're returning
for a second time.

227
00:17:03,220 --> 00:17:06,020
Yu Shi is the CEO now.

228
00:17:07,180 --> 00:17:09,010
Rui is managed by new blood.

229
00:17:11,819 --> 00:17:13,849
I just joined the company.

230
00:17:14,220 --> 00:17:17,450
My focus will be on you two.

231
00:17:19,020 --> 00:17:20,700
We'll cut to the chase, then.

232
00:17:20,780 --> 00:17:21,770
Sure.

233
00:17:21,869 --> 00:17:22,980
Mr Ding.

234
00:17:23,150 --> 00:17:25,210
What are your plans for us

235
00:17:25,290 --> 00:17:27,780
regarding brand and resources?

236
00:17:29,990 --> 00:17:32,050
What kind of brand do you want?

237
00:17:32,390 --> 00:17:33,500
Pineapple Xpress.

238
00:17:34,990 --> 00:17:36,690
Pineapple Xpress.

239
00:17:36,500 --> 00:17:39,110
[Protein Powder]

240
00:17:40,910 --> 00:17:41,980
There, there.

241
00:17:42,820 --> 00:17:44,210
Cheer up.

242
00:17:44,580 --> 00:17:47,810
You can't force them to stay

243
00:17:47,990 --> 00:17:50,100
if their heart is no longer here.

244
00:17:50,510 --> 00:17:52,900
When Cola first joined us,

245
00:17:52,990 --> 00:17:54,210
I knew

246
00:17:56,220 --> 00:17:58,260
Cloud Live would never be enough

247
00:17:58,390 --> 00:18:00,050
for her.

248
00:18:00,750 --> 00:18:02,950
I think she doesn't know what she wants.

249
00:18:03,060 --> 00:18:05,370
That's why she was so lost

250
00:18:05,450 --> 00:18:07,050
and kept changing sides.

251
00:18:08,860 --> 00:18:10,380
I pity her actually.

252
00:18:14,550 --> 00:18:17,290
Come on. You can always
train new people.

253
00:18:17,420 --> 00:18:18,620
It'll be fine.

254
00:18:22,100 --> 00:18:24,500
It'd be good if they were all like you.

255
00:18:25,750 --> 00:18:28,500
Gentle, caring, kind and understanding.

256
00:18:29,100 --> 00:18:30,290
That would be good.

257
00:18:31,030 --> 00:18:32,210
Jia Yun.

258
00:18:33,100 --> 00:18:34,900
Sometimes I feel as if

259
00:18:34,990 --> 00:18:36,380
I'm a sword.

260
00:18:36,550 --> 00:18:37,930
When I meet people

261
00:18:38,220 --> 00:18:40,690
like Cola, Ding Ding,

262
00:18:41,340 --> 00:18:43,780
Duan Ran, Shen Jiang Tao,

263
00:18:44,670 --> 00:18:46,900
all the people in my life,

264
00:18:47,390 --> 00:18:49,620
be they friends or foes,

265
00:18:50,910 --> 00:18:53,100
are like my grindstones.

266
00:18:54,670 --> 00:18:56,140
The more of them I meet,

267
00:18:56,870 --> 00:18:58,330
the sharper I become.

268
00:19:00,220 --> 00:19:01,740
But you're different.

269
00:19:03,180 --> 00:19:06,330
You're bright and intelligent,

270
00:19:07,060 --> 00:19:08,860
more like a scabbard

271
00:19:09,180 --> 00:19:11,020
that can hide my edge.

272
00:19:14,340 --> 00:19:17,980
Where did you copy these phrases from?

273
00:19:18,630 --> 00:19:21,450
I didn't copy it.
It came from my heart.

274
00:19:22,790 --> 00:19:23,780
Fine.

275
00:19:24,060 --> 00:19:27,660
Since you're so pitiful today,

276
00:19:27,740 --> 00:19:28,930
I'll do you a favour.

277
00:19:32,630 --> 00:19:34,430
Another meeting with Mr Duan Sr?

278
00:19:40,300 --> 00:19:42,920
It's been ages. Will we catch anything?

279
00:19:43,140 --> 00:19:45,740
Quiet. You're scaring the fish away.

280
00:19:47,270 --> 00:19:49,660
Let's chat. It's getting boring.

281
00:19:50,300 --> 00:19:51,870
If you really want to catch some fish,

282
00:19:51,870 --> 00:19:53,580
I'll get us a boat to the sea.

283
00:19:53,670 --> 00:19:55,570
Just cast a net and haul them in.

284
00:19:56,060 --> 00:19:57,450
Is that the same?

285
00:19:59,540 --> 00:20:02,210
Look at us sitting by the sea,

286
00:20:02,620 --> 00:20:05,570
in this beautiful weather
and this sea breeze,

287
00:20:05,940 --> 00:20:09,810
quietly waiting for the fish
to take our baits.

288
00:20:11,030 --> 00:20:12,450
Fishing with a net?

289
00:20:12,580 --> 00:20:15,570
What's the fun in that? It's so easy.

290
00:20:15,790 --> 00:20:19,490
It's nothing compared
to the joy and excitement

291
00:20:19,580 --> 00:20:21,810
of waiting for a catch.

292
00:20:22,790 --> 00:20:24,900
Mum was nagging at me back home.

293
00:20:24,990 --> 00:20:26,900
And now, you're nagging at me too.

294
00:20:28,030 --> 00:20:30,050
You're really hard to please.

295
00:20:30,420 --> 00:20:31,940
If I don't say anything,
you'll say I'm bottled up.

296
00:20:31,940 --> 00:20:34,270
When I say something,
you say I'm nagging.

297
00:20:34,550 --> 00:20:37,010
Alright, fine.
We'll just focus on fishing.

298
00:20:37,340 --> 00:20:40,930
So, did any fish take the bait?

299
00:20:42,220 --> 00:20:43,980
Let me check.

300
00:20:46,990 --> 00:20:49,260
-What fell in?
-Just great.

301
00:20:50,420 --> 00:20:52,020
Our water bottle.

302
00:20:53,180 --> 00:20:56,020
-Oh.
-Clumsy fellow.

303
00:21:02,580 --> 00:21:03,900
Doing business

304
00:21:03,990 --> 00:21:06,850
is not just about money and profit.

305
00:21:06,940 --> 00:21:09,900
Sure, profits can maintain relationships.

306
00:21:09,990 --> 00:21:11,820
But it's not permanent.

307
00:21:11,910 --> 00:21:14,010
You still need the emotional aspect.

308
00:21:14,100 --> 00:21:15,300
You think you and Mr Wu

309
00:21:15,340 --> 00:21:18,970
are totally different people, don't you?

310
00:21:19,300 --> 00:21:20,820
If you can

311
00:21:20,910 --> 00:21:22,740
find a common ground

312
00:21:22,820 --> 00:21:25,210
between you two,

313
00:21:25,340 --> 00:21:27,140
you can establish a friendship.

314
00:21:36,300 --> 00:21:38,690
-Mr Wu.
-So, Jia Yun set me up with you?

315
00:21:39,550 --> 00:21:41,660
I couldn't get you to meet me.

316
00:21:41,790 --> 00:21:43,290
I had no choice.

317
00:21:43,580 --> 00:21:45,460
Why are we sitting here
instead of the sofa area?

318
00:21:45,460 --> 00:21:46,460
That area was full

319
00:21:46,510 --> 00:21:47,710
when I arrived.

320
00:21:47,790 --> 00:21:49,370
But now it's empty.

321
00:21:49,450 --> 00:21:50,510
Do you want to change tables?

322
00:21:50,510 --> 00:21:52,060
No, it's fine.
We'll just sit here.

323
00:21:52,060 --> 00:21:53,520
It won't take long anyway.

324
00:21:58,390 --> 00:21:59,380
Mr Wu.

325
00:22:00,220 --> 00:22:01,500
I'm really sorry.

326
00:22:01,630 --> 00:22:02,670
I have no choice

327
00:22:02,750 --> 00:22:04,570
but to do this.

328
00:22:04,670 --> 00:22:05,660
Chen Lang.

329
00:22:05,750 --> 00:22:07,690
Cloud Live has just been revived.

330
00:22:07,820 --> 00:22:09,620
We still have our reservations.

331
00:22:10,390 --> 00:22:11,630
I suggest that you work with

332
00:22:11,630 --> 00:22:13,210
some small-scale suppliers.

333
00:22:13,210 --> 00:22:14,670
That would be a good start.

334
00:22:15,030 --> 00:22:15,980
Yes.

335
00:22:16,060 --> 00:22:17,030
After you build yourself up,

336
00:22:17,030 --> 00:22:18,760
we can then collaborate again.

337
00:22:19,220 --> 00:22:20,210
Mr Wu.

338
00:22:20,300 --> 00:22:21,330
You told me this

339
00:22:21,420 --> 00:22:23,610
over the phone previously.

340
00:22:23,700 --> 00:22:25,200
I haven't forgotten.

341
00:22:25,550 --> 00:22:27,610
But the reason I want to meet you today

342
00:22:27,870 --> 00:22:29,620
is not about work.

343
00:22:30,100 --> 00:22:31,540
I just want to

344
00:22:31,630 --> 00:22:33,090
get to know you as a friend.

345
00:22:33,180 --> 00:22:34,530
Get to know me?

346
00:22:38,630 --> 00:22:40,330
If you weren't

347
00:22:40,550 --> 00:22:41,930
so clumsy

348
00:22:42,630 --> 00:22:44,260
as to lose our water bottle,

349
00:22:44,340 --> 00:22:46,620
we wouldn't end up like this.

350
00:22:46,990 --> 00:22:49,500
Let's take a rest under the tree.

351
00:22:53,910 --> 00:22:55,620
This weather is killing me.

352
00:22:55,900 --> 00:22:57,410
Sit down here, you brat.

353
00:22:59,820 --> 00:23:04,020
You know, we're both lucky people.

354
00:23:04,550 --> 00:23:06,270
When lucky people come together,

355
00:23:06,270 --> 00:23:08,170
good things are bound to happen.

356
00:23:08,270 --> 00:23:09,320
I hope so.

357
00:23:10,270 --> 00:23:11,670
The thirst is killing me.

358
00:23:11,740 --> 00:23:13,660
It's killing me too.

359
00:23:16,060 --> 00:23:17,050
Dad.

360
00:23:17,700 --> 00:23:18,760
Ice-cream seller.

361
00:23:18,910 --> 00:23:20,570
Ice-cream seller.
Over here.

362
00:23:20,700 --> 00:23:21,740
Hi there.

363
00:23:22,100 --> 00:23:23,210
This is great.

364
00:23:23,460 --> 00:23:24,500
Heaven opens a window.

365
00:23:24,500 --> 00:23:26,290
-You want ice-cream?
-You bet.

366
00:23:27,790 --> 00:23:28,930
Let me see.

367
00:23:29,390 --> 00:23:30,850
What flavours do you have?

368
00:23:31,030 --> 00:23:32,580
Green bean, milk,

369
00:23:32,670 --> 00:23:34,740
and also ice bar.
Take your pick.

370
00:23:34,990 --> 00:23:37,410
In that case,
give me two of each.

371
00:23:38,670 --> 00:23:40,330
Buddy,
I suggest

372
00:23:40,420 --> 00:23:41,810
you don't eat too much.

373
00:23:41,940 --> 00:23:43,340
Ice-cream may be nice

374
00:23:43,420 --> 00:23:45,130
in this weather,

375
00:23:45,220 --> 00:23:46,810
but it's bad for health.

376
00:23:47,010 --> 00:23:48,340
Others would be happy to sell more.

377
00:23:48,340 --> 00:23:49,800
But you want me to buy less.

378
00:23:49,990 --> 00:23:51,460
Small businesses like mine

379
00:23:51,460 --> 00:23:52,510
are all about heart.

380
00:23:52,510 --> 00:23:53,500
If you get sick,

381
00:23:53,660 --> 00:23:55,200
I'd feel really sorry.

382
00:23:56,270 --> 00:23:57,210
It's rare to meet

383
00:23:57,290 --> 00:23:59,380
a seller as kind as you.

384
00:24:00,990 --> 00:24:01,980
Ran Ran.

385
00:24:02,900 --> 00:24:04,100
Get me one green bean.

386
00:24:04,150 --> 00:24:05,780
-I'm holding it.
-Sure.

387
00:24:06,910 --> 00:24:07,900
Young man.

388
00:24:08,420 --> 00:24:10,290
How much for all these?

389
00:24:10,580 --> 00:24:12,570
Ten fifty yuan.

390
00:24:12,690 --> 00:24:14,930
Since it's fate that brought us here,

391
00:24:15,060 --> 00:24:16,030
I'll give you a discount.

392
00:24:16,030 --> 00:24:17,570
Ten yuan will do.

393
00:24:17,990 --> 00:24:19,060
You're too kind.

394
00:24:19,150 --> 00:24:20,130
Is that okay?

395
00:24:20,220 --> 00:24:21,930
The weather is very hot today.

396
00:24:22,150 --> 00:24:23,500
This must be hard work.

397
00:24:24,220 --> 00:24:25,660
With the high inflation,

398
00:24:25,990 --> 00:24:27,030
how much do you make

399
00:24:27,030 --> 00:24:28,100
selling ice-cream?

400
00:24:28,100 --> 00:24:29,780
I'm not doing this to get rich.

401
00:24:29,860 --> 00:24:31,720
I'm just supplying my old friends

402
00:24:31,790 --> 00:24:33,720
with their favourite ice-creams.

403
00:24:33,790 --> 00:24:34,780
Impressive.

404
00:24:35,270 --> 00:24:36,330
Ran Ran, pay him.

405
00:24:36,420 --> 00:24:38,090
-Yes.
-Please scan here.

406
00:24:38,180 --> 00:24:39,700
Since fate has

407
00:24:39,790 --> 00:24:40,990
brought us together,

408
00:24:41,390 --> 00:24:42,520
I should pay you duly

409
00:24:42,580 --> 00:24:44,290
and not a cent less.

410
00:24:45,910 --> 00:24:47,100
Surely, you jest.

411
00:24:47,750 --> 00:24:49,140
Actually, I think

412
00:24:49,220 --> 00:24:50,810
we have a lot in common.

413
00:24:50,940 --> 00:24:51,930
Really.

414
00:24:52,740 --> 00:24:55,050
Mr Wu, may I ask

415
00:24:55,220 --> 00:24:56,860
where you are from?

416
00:24:58,300 --> 00:24:59,370
Wanbei.

417
00:24:59,450 --> 00:25:01,020
What a coincidence.

418
00:25:01,340 --> 00:25:02,930
I'm from Subei.

419
00:25:03,180 --> 00:25:04,100
Really?

420
00:25:04,180 --> 00:25:05,220
That's pretty close.

421
00:25:05,220 --> 00:25:06,210
Yes.

422
00:25:06,870 --> 00:25:07,980
My house

423
00:25:08,140 --> 00:25:10,050
is very near to Anhui.

424
00:25:10,150 --> 00:25:11,860
It's a small village.

425
00:25:12,210 --> 00:25:14,780
We were very poor.

426
00:25:15,700 --> 00:25:16,940
Can I ask you a random question?

427
00:25:16,940 --> 00:25:18,740
Can you guess where I graduated?

428
00:25:20,870 --> 00:25:24,070
Don't tell me you're from Tsinghua
or Peking University.

429
00:25:25,150 --> 00:25:26,380
Really?

430
00:25:26,700 --> 00:25:28,020
You guessed it.

431
00:25:28,220 --> 00:25:30,900
I'm a computer science graduate
from Tsinghua.

432
00:25:31,870 --> 00:25:34,390
I ran a small business in Beijing
after graduation,

433
00:25:34,390 --> 00:25:35,300
failed,

434
00:25:35,390 --> 00:25:37,140
then came to Xiamen

435
00:25:37,300 --> 00:25:39,900
and got started in women's fashion.

436
00:25:40,700 --> 00:25:42,570
I was from a poor family

437
00:25:42,880 --> 00:25:44,330
with many older sisters.

438
00:25:44,780 --> 00:25:46,510
My parents only bought clothes for them.

439
00:25:46,510 --> 00:25:49,570
I had to wear their hand-me-downs.

440
00:25:49,670 --> 00:25:51,190
Who would've known?

441
00:25:51,270 --> 00:25:54,730
Right? After all, I was a top student
back in the day,

442
00:25:54,820 --> 00:25:56,470
and was somewhat famous.

443
00:25:56,550 --> 00:25:58,390
Wearing flowery outfits everyday

444
00:25:58,390 --> 00:26:01,170
was so embarrassing.

445
00:26:01,270 --> 00:26:02,570
That's not too bad.

446
00:26:03,630 --> 00:26:05,020
I then bought some bleach

447
00:26:05,020 --> 00:26:07,140
and soaked my clothes in it

448
00:26:07,220 --> 00:26:08,580
until the colours faded.

449
00:26:08,580 --> 00:26:10,660
But wasn't it still flowery?

450
00:26:11,460 --> 00:26:14,210
At least they weren't so conspicuous.

451
00:26:14,340 --> 00:26:16,330
Here's the thing,

452
00:26:16,420 --> 00:26:18,150
it turned out kind of nice on me.

453
00:26:19,270 --> 00:26:20,750
But when it comes to alterations,

454
00:26:20,750 --> 00:26:22,780
I have more experience than you.

455
00:26:23,180 --> 00:26:24,840
You had a similar experience?

456
00:26:28,270 --> 00:26:29,260
Ran Ran.

457
00:26:29,990 --> 00:26:32,190
Did you notice how the ice-cream seller

458
00:26:32,790 --> 00:26:34,170
conducts his business?

459
00:26:35,820 --> 00:26:37,660
I think he's a good businessman.

460
00:26:38,270 --> 00:26:39,630
He cares about his customers.

461
00:26:39,630 --> 00:26:40,810
He's full of warmth.

462
00:26:41,150 --> 00:26:42,420
His customers are willing

463
00:26:42,420 --> 00:26:43,750
to give him their money.

464
00:26:46,060 --> 00:26:48,390
Providing comfort is the basis
of business.

465
00:26:48,390 --> 00:26:50,660
But many businessmen these days

466
00:26:51,780 --> 00:26:54,050
only want to maximise their profit.

467
00:26:55,790 --> 00:26:57,920
Did I tell you about your grandfather?

468
00:26:58,220 --> 00:26:59,210
Yes, you did.

469
00:26:59,700 --> 00:27:01,680
He was a street vendor.

470
00:27:01,870 --> 00:27:04,020
He's a vendor in the mountain area.

471
00:27:05,820 --> 00:27:07,670
He gathered chicken and duck feathers

472
00:27:07,670 --> 00:27:08,930
in exchange for goods.

473
00:27:10,100 --> 00:27:13,210
Bartering is the oldest form of sales.

474
00:27:13,820 --> 00:27:15,080
Do you know what it took

475
00:27:15,100 --> 00:27:16,420
to do business back then?

476
00:27:16,420 --> 00:27:19,400
It took rapport and relationships.

477
00:27:22,100 --> 00:27:23,900
Those were simple times.

478
00:27:24,420 --> 00:27:27,980
There's so much plotting and scheming
nowadays.

479
00:27:28,340 --> 00:27:29,940
There are still exceptions.

480
00:27:30,460 --> 00:27:32,980
Me? I try to pass the kindness on.

481
00:27:34,690 --> 00:27:37,570
Ran Ran, you're still young.

482
00:27:38,270 --> 00:27:40,470
You must be able to withstand setbacks.

483
00:27:40,940 --> 00:27:42,170
But most importantly,

484
00:27:42,170 --> 00:27:44,330
you need a clear goal to fight for.

485
00:27:49,390 --> 00:27:50,380
Dad.

486
00:27:51,410 --> 00:27:52,980
I know what you and Mum mean.

487
00:27:53,060 --> 00:27:54,930
My time at home

488
00:27:56,550 --> 00:27:57,660
got me thinking.

489
00:27:59,420 --> 00:28:01,020
Since I came back from the UK,

490
00:28:01,940 --> 00:28:04,930
I've been doing everything my way.

491
00:28:05,990 --> 00:28:07,740
I was kind of wilful.

492
00:28:09,300 --> 00:28:11,500
Who wasn't wilful when they were young?

493
00:28:11,870 --> 00:28:13,170
I was wilful, too.

494
00:28:13,820 --> 00:28:14,990
That's not the problem.

495
00:28:14,990 --> 00:28:17,860
The key is having a clear goal

496
00:28:18,040 --> 00:28:20,450
and knowing when to cut your losses.

497
00:28:23,150 --> 00:28:25,660
Take my advice, son.

498
00:28:26,100 --> 00:28:27,820
If you don't find anything suitable,

499
00:28:27,820 --> 00:28:29,100
come back to QE.

500
00:28:29,580 --> 00:28:31,260
Just come back to QE.

501
00:28:31,420 --> 00:28:32,620
How about that?

502
00:28:35,910 --> 00:28:37,210
What can I do

503
00:28:37,510 --> 00:28:38,780
if I go back to QE?

504
00:28:39,380 --> 00:28:41,380
You can start off as a floor manager.

505
00:28:43,030 --> 00:28:44,850
The main duty of a floor manager

506
00:28:44,940 --> 00:28:47,740
is to maintain merchant-shopper
relationships.

507
00:28:47,990 --> 00:28:49,340
It's a role that requires

508
00:28:49,340 --> 00:28:50,810
high EQ and decisiveness.

509
00:28:51,090 --> 00:28:53,380
As well as warmth, like you said.

510
00:28:53,910 --> 00:28:55,260
It's not an easy job.

511
00:28:55,750 --> 00:28:57,950
The job will be a great training for you.

512
00:28:59,870 --> 00:29:02,700
If I return to QE, it means I have to
talk to Uncle Shen.

513
00:29:02,700 --> 00:29:04,030
What's wrong with that?

514
00:29:04,180 --> 00:29:06,040
Are you afraid he'll put you down?

515
00:29:06,180 --> 00:29:07,170
He won't.

516
00:29:07,300 --> 00:29:08,580
He's not that kind of person.

517
00:29:08,580 --> 00:29:09,580
I know him.

518
00:29:09,670 --> 00:29:10,580
We may disagree

519
00:29:10,670 --> 00:29:12,130
on how to run a business,

520
00:29:12,220 --> 00:29:13,810
but it's nothing personal.

521
00:29:15,660 --> 00:29:17,820
I think you should change your attitude.

522
00:29:17,820 --> 00:29:18,810
Son.

523
00:29:19,300 --> 00:29:22,020
Let go of your ego and your status.

524
00:29:22,290 --> 00:29:23,330
Can you do that?

525
00:29:26,140 --> 00:29:28,270
I was supposed to visit
a manufacturer

526
00:29:28,580 --> 00:29:32,330
to look at some samples today.

527
00:29:32,410 --> 00:29:34,410
Looks like I won't be able to make it.

528
00:29:36,260 --> 00:29:38,260
Time sure flies.

529
00:29:38,670 --> 00:29:40,700
Thank you for your time.

530
00:29:40,790 --> 00:29:42,200
I truly appreciate it.

531
00:29:42,550 --> 00:29:45,580
Well, I got to see a side of you

532
00:29:45,670 --> 00:29:47,000
I've never seen before.

533
00:29:47,070 --> 00:29:47,970
As for your

534
00:29:48,060 --> 00:29:50,420
suggestions and ideas today,

535
00:29:50,510 --> 00:29:52,690
I'll think about it tonight.

536
00:29:54,030 --> 00:29:55,790
Tomorrow, I'll talk to the tailors

537
00:29:55,790 --> 00:29:56,730
at the factory.

538
00:29:56,820 --> 00:29:59,620
If it's viable,

539
00:29:59,700 --> 00:30:01,500
I'll definitely see it through.

540
00:30:04,670 --> 00:30:05,810
Mr Wu.

541
00:30:06,060 --> 00:30:07,500
I told you

542
00:30:07,620 --> 00:30:09,050
this meeting is not about work,

543
00:30:09,050 --> 00:30:11,660
but in the end, we still talk about it.

544
00:30:11,750 --> 00:30:13,210
Chen Lang.

545
00:30:14,300 --> 00:30:15,210
I know

546
00:30:15,300 --> 00:30:17,180
you are passionate about your job.

547
00:30:17,180 --> 00:30:18,980
I know where you're coming from.

548
00:30:22,340 --> 00:30:23,620
Thank you, Mr Wu.

549
00:30:30,630 --> 00:30:31,690
Uncle Shen.

550
00:30:32,810 --> 00:30:35,010
I'm here to apologise.

551
00:30:35,580 --> 00:30:37,320
I was too impulsive.

552
00:30:37,940 --> 00:30:39,610
Although I did not push Yu Shi,

553
00:30:39,700 --> 00:30:42,570
I did indirectly cause his injury.

554
00:30:42,940 --> 00:30:44,290
I should apologise.

555
00:30:45,990 --> 00:30:48,850
Recognising your mistake

556
00:30:48,940 --> 00:30:50,900
and apologising

557
00:30:51,990 --> 00:30:53,780
makes you a real man.

558
00:30:55,260 --> 00:30:56,530
I...

559
00:30:57,630 --> 00:30:59,090
Actually I came here today

560
00:30:59,510 --> 00:31:01,570
to ask you for a favour.

561
00:31:02,390 --> 00:31:04,190
I hope you'll grant me this wish.

562
00:31:04,820 --> 00:31:06,370
You want to return to Rui?

563
00:31:07,510 --> 00:31:08,780
I want to go to QE

564
00:31:09,150 --> 00:31:10,810
and become a floor manager.

565
00:31:11,390 --> 00:31:15,530
My problem was being overly ambitious

566
00:31:16,220 --> 00:31:19,410
without any real experience or foundation.

567
00:31:20,150 --> 00:31:22,530
So I think I should start at the bottom.

568
00:31:22,820 --> 00:31:23,930
Hold on.

569
00:31:28,810 --> 00:31:31,810
Mr Liu. Can you come to my office?

570
00:31:32,400 --> 00:31:35,350
[Shapowei Art Zone]

571
00:31:35,440 --> 00:31:39,750
[Vine]

